==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prod
<hw>Prod</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gael. & Ir.
<ets>brod</ets> goad, prickle, sting, and E. <ets>brad</ets>, also W.
<ets>procio</ets> to poke, thrust.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A pointed instrument for pricking or puncturing, as
a goad, an awl, a skewer, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A prick or stab which a pointed
instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A light kind of crossbow; -- in the sense, often
spelled <xex>prodd</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prod</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prod
<hw>Prod</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Prodded</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prodding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To thrust some pointed
instrument into; to prick with something sharp; <as>as, to <ex>prod</ex>
a soldier with a bayonet; to <ex>prod</ex> oxen</as>; hence, to goad, to
incite, to worry; <as>as, to <ex>prod</ex> a student</as>.</def>
<rj><au>H. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prodd</ent>⟦br⟧
